Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.08,0:00:02.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name's Conan Edogawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.58,0:00:05.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,High school student Shinichi was forced\Nto take a drug that shrunk him!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.58,0:00:08.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although smaller, my mind remains\Nthat of a sharp detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.58,0:00:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A review of the last episode\Nwill accompany the theme song!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.13,0:00:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a big ship, but there's\Nalways only one truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.74,0:00:21.19,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The first end of the century in 100 years{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.83,0:00:27.41,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When told to cry, I laughed instead{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.03,0:00:39.50,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The first end of the century\Nin a long, long time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.18,0:00:45.59,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We're leaping into a wide open world{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.17,0:00:52.18,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The things I tried to\Nunderstand as a child{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.34,0:00:58.61,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}remain a mystery even as an adult{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.89,0:01:04.61,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm neither a hotshot\Nnor especially great{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.89,0:01:11.03,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All I understand is\Nthe pounding of my heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.19,0:01:16.92,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's neither an answer nor the truth{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.20,0:01:23.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All I have faith in is\Nthe pounding of my heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.29,0:01:28.51,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That and nothing else {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.50,0:01:48.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were nearly stranded on an island
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.30,0:01:51.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,before we were picked up by a ship\Nthat the Hatamoto family had reserved.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.09,0:01:56.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Including the three of us and the butler,\Nthere were only 10 people onboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.51,0:01:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On our way back to land,\NHatamoto Gozo,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.60,0:02:01.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,head of the Hatamoto family,\Nwas murdered in his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.76,0:02:03.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The main suspect was Hatamoto Takeshi,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.60,0:02:05.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who entered the family\Nby marrying Hatamoto Natsue.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.11,0:02:08.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He turned out to be\Nthe son of Zaiki Isao,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.65,0:02:13.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who killed himself after Gozo took over\Nhis company 10 years earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.24,0:02:17.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since he had a motive, everyone decided\Nto lock Takeshi in a storeroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.45,0:02:21.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looked like the case was closed,\Nbut there was more to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.78,0:02:25.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hatamoto Tatsuo, Akie's husband,\Nwas found dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.01,0:02:27.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Takeshi had escaped\Nfrom the storeroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.08,0:02:35.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Luxury Liner Murders, Part 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.66,0:02:45.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tatsuo!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.37,0:02:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Akie...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.14,0:02:49.65,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hatamoto Akie
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.76,0:02:48.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's your fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.04,0:02:49.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.33,0:02:50.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This never would've happened
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.38,0:02:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if you hadn't brought Takeshi\Ninto our family!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.08,0:02:55.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you have to say for yourself?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.32,0:02:57.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You certainly are lucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.32,0:02:58.64,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hatamoto Kitaro\NHatamoto Ichiro
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.72,0:03:00.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that Takeshi's killed Father,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.30,0:03:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all of his fortune belongs to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.47,0:03:07.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious!\NI don't care about his fortune!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.38,0:03:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're still not certain that Takeshi-san\Nis the one responsible, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.07,0:03:15.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.99,0:03:19.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The storeroom door was unlocked\Nwhen we checked it out, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.86,0:03:22.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.53,0:03:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He couldn't have gotten out
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.91,0:03:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,unless someone unlocked it\Nfrom the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.50,0:03:28.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.46,0:03:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were no signs of damage\Non the door, either...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.58,0:03:33.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So if someone did unlock it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.04,0:03:35.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then he has an accomplice in this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.41,0:03:49.23,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hatamoto Takeshi
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.73,0:03:53.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So let me get this straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.02,0:03:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the time of Tatsuo-san's murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.90,0:03:59.36,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hatamoto Joji
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.36,0:03:59.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the three of you were alone\Nin your private rooms,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.03,0:04:03.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while you two were together\Nin your shared room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.37,0:04:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I couldn't sleep,\Nso I went for a little walk...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.47,0:04:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that just\Nlike the first murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.41,0:04:13.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,aside from everyone\Nwho was with Natsue-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.41,0:04:15.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nobody here has an alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.41,0:04:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You gotta be kidding me!\NMy husband just died!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.38,0:04:21.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why am I a suspect?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.63,0:04:26.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who's\Nhappiest to see him dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.18,0:04:32.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that you've been\Nseeing other men!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.93,0:04:36.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You had a big enough reason\Nto kill Grandfather!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.69,0:04:39.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who wanted\Nhis inheritance the most!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.40,0:04:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it, you two! Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.79,0:04:50.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you draw that, Ichiro-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.45,0:04:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Natsue-san, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.12,0:04:56.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And your son Ichiro isn't exempt either!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.13,0:04:57.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.01,0:04:59.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure he was pretty pissed
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.76,0:05:02.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after Grandfather tore up\Nhis prize-winning drawing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.21,0:05:07.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was Father's fault--\Nhe never recognized this boy's talent!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.64,0:05:10.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tatsuo always made fun of you, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.56,0:05:12.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Depressed introvert"\Nand stuff like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.89,0:05:16.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I didn't kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.19,0:05:19.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the one who wanted to be\Nfree of Grandfather the most...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.28,0:05:22.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was you, Uncle Kitaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.98,0:05:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.73,0:05:26.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro! Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.66,0:05:27.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.74,0:05:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you be alright by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.54,0:05:34.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine. I'm not\Na weakling like my father!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.37,0:05:35.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.74,0:05:38.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mr. Butler...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.17,0:05:41.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen\Nbetween Kitaro-san and Gozo-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.42,0:05:45.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kitaro-sama has wanted to leave\Nthe Hatamoto family for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.18,0:05:49.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He says he doesn't have the ambition\Nto run the family company.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.97,0:05:53.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gozo-sama was greatly\Nopposed to the idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.60,0:05:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But even if he wasn't against it,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.86,0:05:59.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think his wife Mariko-sama\Nwould have allowed it either...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.94,0:06:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.73,0:06:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been 20 minutes, but Ichiro\Nstill isn't back from the restroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.74,0:06:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me Takeshi got him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.45,0:06:17.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down! Stay where you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.63,0:06:21.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! But Ichiro isn't back yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.04,0:06:21.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.97,0:06:23.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't leave the room, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.62,0:06:26.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan and Ran! Are you there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.69,0:06:27.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.94,0:06:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.35,0:06:31.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to the electrical room!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.19,0:06:33.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You two head for the restroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.77,0:06:36.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The restrooms were this way, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.37,0:06:37.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.95,0:06:40.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't that Ichiro-san's voice?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.94,0:06:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.95,0:06:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.54,0:06:49.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.17,0:06:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My leg!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.96,0:06:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there, Ichiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.96,0:06:55.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's alright! The wound isn't deep!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.62,0:06:57.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to bandage it up right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.26,0:06:59.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get the first-aid kit!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.09,0:07:02.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who did this to you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.13,0:07:03.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.34,0:07:07.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The lights suddenly went out\Nand then I sensed someone come in...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.94,0:07:09.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then they stabbed me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.89,0:07:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.11,0:07:17.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...My knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.03,0:07:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you did this, Joji!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.03,0:07:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.15,0:07:24.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was with you all in the dining room\Nwhen the power went out!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.95,0:07:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't have done this!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.58,0:07:28.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.16,0:07:30.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is only one person\Nwho could have done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.75,0:07:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.41,0:07:36.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not necessarily the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.67,0:07:40.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let Natsue-san and Ran take care\Nof Ichiro-kun's bandage.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.01,0:07:43.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like the rest of you to come\Nto the electrical room with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.81,0:07:48.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.02,0:07:50.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Have a look for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.27,0:07:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.81,0:07:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a type of timing device.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.86,0:07:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This one is simple enough\Nfor anyone to set up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.78,0:08:02.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You attach a heavy weight to the breaker,\Nbalance it around a fulcrum,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.28,0:08:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then put a candle in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.22,0:08:09.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After enough time passes,\Nthe rope burns apart,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.36,0:08:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which causes the weight\Nto pull down on the breaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.04,0:08:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Judging from how much\Nof the candle has melted,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.33,0:08:16.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this was all set up quite a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.67,0:08:21.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, any one of you could\Nbe responsible for the power outage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.13,0:08:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, I'll take the responsibility\Nof finding Takeshi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.14,0:08:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until I do, I don't want any of you\Nto take a step out of the dining room!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.65,0:08:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does it hurt, Ichiro?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.87,0:08:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.87,0:08:51.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe we've looked this\Nhard but still haven't found him!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.45,0:08:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then maybe he's not\Non the ship anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.87,0:08:56.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think we've\Nsearched everywhere yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.45,0:09:00.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like everyone's rooms!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.08,0:09:09.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not in Kitaro-san's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.62,0:09:15.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These two seem to have rather\Ndifferent personalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.29,0:09:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is their marriage holding up well?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.26,0:09:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. They're both cousins,\Nand although it may not look like it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.13,0:09:24.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they've been good friends\Nsince they were little.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.03,0:09:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're cousins and they're married?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.74,0:09:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.50,0:09:32.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gozo-sama was extremely\Nopposed to them, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.67,0:09:34.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Them, too"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.84,0:09:43.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't look like he's\Nin Joji-san's room, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.09,0:09:47.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, is this his knife case?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.31,0:09:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.56,0:09:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two of his knives are missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.44,0:09:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.56,0:09:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One knife we found right\Nafter Ichiro-kun was attacked,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.57,0:10:00.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but where's the other one?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.03,0:10:06.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This must be Ichiro-san's room!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.04,0:10:08.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? These are his drawings!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.29,0:10:10.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's no reason to\Nenter the room carelessly!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.83,0:10:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi-kun could be hiding\Nin here with a weapon!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.37,0:10:16.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, he's really good!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.84,0:10:20.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows, maybe there's a drawing\Nof the murder scene here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.84,0:10:23.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.14,0:10:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey now, don't touch those!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.11,0:10:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.64,0:10:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not in here, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.61,0:10:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would seem not.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.65,0:10:40.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.49,0:10:42.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Charcoal. You use it for rough sketches.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.32,0:10:44.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.15,0:10:47.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, get the lead out. We're moving on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.37,0:10:49.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.91,0:10:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an ordinary eraser.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.71,0:10:54.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.34,0:11:00.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wasn't in our rooms\Nor in Natsue-san's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.67,0:11:03.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All that's left is\NAkie-san's room here...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.10,0:11:08.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess he's not on the ship anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.13,0:11:12.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find something?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.95,0:11:14.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Nothing at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.99,0:11:16.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.59,0:11:18.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's return to the dining room for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.68,0:11:25.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mr. Butler.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.67,0:11:27.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know if...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.35,0:11:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did that ever happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.98,0:11:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you find out?\NOnly Gozo-sama and I know about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.30,0:11:39.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I'm right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.57,0:11:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first incident,\Nin which Mr. Gozo was killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.32,0:11:46.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bread found near the body,\Nand the location of the murder weapon...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.12,0:11:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The second incident,\Nin which Tatsuo-san was killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.67,0:11:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The splash and thud sounds I heard\Nat the time of the murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.46,0:11:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The person who unlocked\Nthe storeroom door...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.38,0:12:00.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then the third incident, in which\NIchiro-san was stabbed in the dark...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.63,0:12:04.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each of these mysteries is connected\Nby a single thread!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.59,0:12:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, come here a sec!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.19,0:12:17.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.60,0:12:20.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find something?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.70,0:12:28.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.49,0:12:33.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Where's Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.28,0:12:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has something important to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.99,0:12:38.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so he wants everyone to come\Nto Akie-san's room in 10 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.12,0:12:40.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something important to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.56,0:12:43.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell the others!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.80,0:12:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.46,0:12:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The old man's voice is #59...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.63,0:12:55.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know who did it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.45,0:13:00.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Someone on this ship was\Nresponsible for all three incidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.89,0:13:03.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.52,0:13:05.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's obviously him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.30,0:13:06.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was Takeshi's doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.87,0:13:08.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, just calm down...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.95,0:13:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before I reveal the killer's name,\Nlet us look at the incidents again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.31,0:13:16.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First was Incident #1, in which\NMr. Gozo was murdered in his room,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.62,0:13:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which had been locked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.83,0:13:22.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From the fact that there\Nwas blood on the doorframe,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.23,0:13:25.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Gozo likely escaped back into\Nhis room after he was stabbed outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.97,0:13:30.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He then locked the door,\Nbut fell lifeless soon after.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.81,0:13:34.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We later found a flower on the ground\Nin front of the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.25,0:13:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Takeshi was wearing it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.02,0:13:39.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means he did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.47,0:13:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there is one strange detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.68,0:13:45.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though Mr. Gozo was\Nstabbed outside his room,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.94,0:13:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there were no blood marks\Nin the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.24,0:13:50.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure the killer\Ndidn't wipe it up
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.57,0:13:53.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to delay us from\Ndiscovering the corpse?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.20,0:13:54.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not refuting that fact--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.99,0:13:59.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just saying that the flower fell\Nafter the blood was wiped up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.24,0:14:01.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can understand if the\Nkiller accidentally dropped it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.16,0:14:03.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while stabbing the victim\Nand then escaping...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.70,0:14:05.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the killer meticulously\Nwiped up the blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.46,0:14:10.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By leaving the flower there,\Neveryone would've noticed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.13,0:14:12.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially if it was dropped\Nduring the middle of cleaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.93,0:14:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the killer purposely\Nleft the flower on the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.92,0:14:19.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in order to make\NTakeshi-san look guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.00,0:14:24.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next is Incident #2, in which\NTatsuo-san was murdered on the deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.25,0:14:26.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike the first incident\Nwith its flower
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.84,0:14:29.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the third incident\Nwith its fancy set-up,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.57,0:14:32.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this incident lacked\Nany sort of artificiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.03,0:14:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If these were all indeed\Ndone by the same person,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.89,0:14:42.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my guess is that the\N2nd murder was an unplanned one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.99,0:14:46.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, why was Tatsuo-san murdered?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.47,0:14:49.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The answer to that question\Nis in this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.90,0:14:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's my knife case!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.87,0:14:56.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a look. Two knives are missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.16,0:14:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We found one of them\Nat the scene of Incident #3,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.12,0:15:00.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but where did the other one go?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.76,0:15:05.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The main point here is in\Nthe two sounds that Conan heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.59,0:15:09.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The thud was likely the sound\Nof the killer striking Tatsuo-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.47,0:15:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but what was the splash\Nthat came before it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.80,0:15:14.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's what I'm thinking--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.63,0:15:19.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the splash sound was the\Nother knife from this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.55,0:15:22.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Tatsuo-san just happened\Nto see it thrown overboard,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.43,0:15:25.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the killer could have killed\Nhim to keep things quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.61,0:15:27.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would make the most sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.82,0:15:32.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Takeshi vanished from the storeroom\Nafter the 2nd incident!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.61,0:15:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Takeshi is the\Nmost suspicious here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.50,0:15:39.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that storeroom door\Nwas locked from the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.91,0:15:42.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Escape would have been impossible
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.08,0:15:42.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,unless someone unlocked it for him!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.21,0:15:44.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who was it then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.87,0:15:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who opened it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.64,0:15:49.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.56,0:15:52.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tatsuo-san's murder wasn't\Npart of the killer's plan,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.10,0:15:55.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and it took place\Nwhile Takeshi-san was locked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.73,0:15:58.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer worked so hard to\Nmake Takeshi-san look guilty,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.61,0:16:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but this 2nd murder would do just\Nthe opposite and prove his innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.25,0:16:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the killer unlocked the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.41,0:16:08.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This was done to make it\Nlook like Takeshi-san
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.87,0:16:11.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,had the ability to murder\NTatsuo-san, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.52,0:16:14.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did Takeshi-san run away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.87,0:16:17.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! We still haven't found him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.04,0:16:19.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's have him explain that himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.34,0:16:25.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi-san. Why don't you\Nstop hiding and come out?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.17,0:16:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's in this room?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.43,0:16:30.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.31,0:16:39.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.98,0:16:44.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, tell us what happened\Nwhen you escaped from the storeroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.43,0:16:48.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought something\Nhappened to Natsue...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.49,0:16:49.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't stand around doing nothing,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.91,0:16:53.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and as I was pounding on the door,\Nit suddenly unlocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.49,0:16:54.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ran out of there!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.92,0:16:57.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then when I went up to the deck...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.37,0:17:00.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi did it again!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.10,0:17:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tatsuo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.38,0:17:04.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Realizing that I would be blamed again,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.96,0:17:07.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ran into Akie-san's room,\Nwhose door just happened to be open.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.26,0:17:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, I stayed inside\Nthe closet the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.08,0:17:14.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the person who stabbed\NIchiro-san during Incident #3
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.34,0:17:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,wasn't him either...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.27,0:17:17.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who was it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.85,0:17:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would they do something\Nthis horrible to Ichiro?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.44,0:17:24.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because the killer made a big mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.60,0:17:25.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.39,0:17:28.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Unlocking the storeroom door.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.66,0:17:32.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer had managed\Nto frame Takeshi-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.66,0:17:36.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but now it looked like he had\Nan accomplice who had let him out!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.99,0:17:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't until then that anyone\Nstarted to suspect the real killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.87,0:17:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Flustered, the murderer\Ncame up with a scheme
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.46,0:17:46.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to avoid any further suspicion...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.63,0:17:50.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Incident #3, in which Ichiro-san\Nwas attacked in the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.63,0:17:57.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was in this incident that\Nthe killer dug his own grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.06,0:18:02.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the darkness, the killer shouldn't\Nhave been able to see Ichiro-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.77,0:18:06.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, he was clearly able to see\NIchiro-kun well enough to stab him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.77,0:18:08.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.77,0:18:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moreover, the weapon was found\Nlying at the scene of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.40,0:18:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike the first two incidents,\Nthe attacker didn't leave with the weapon!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.29,0:18:21.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, the attacker couldn't\Nhave left with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.54,0:18:26.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, he couldn't go anywhere\Nwith his injured leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.80,0:18:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't mean to say--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.39,0:18:30.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.76,0:18:33.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The person who stabbed him...\Nwas Ichiro-kun himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.89,0:18:38.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the one who killed\NMr. Gozo and Tatsuo-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.73,0:18:43.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was you, Ichiro-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.55,0:18:46.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.01,0:18:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason you put the lights out
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.14,0:18:52.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was because you didn't want\Nto identify your attacker.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.65,0:18:58.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you said it was Takeshi-san\Nand then he was found innocent later,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.35,0:19:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then all the suspicion\Nwould fall onto you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.07,0:19:03.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is all conjecture!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.10,0:19:06.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any evidence\Nthat Ichiro's the murderer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.82,0:19:08.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.99,0:19:14.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The piece of bread that was\Nfound near Mr. Gozo's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.26,0:19:16.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A piece of bread?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.96,0:19:18.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro-san is an art student.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.96,0:19:22.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And right before Mr. Gozo was murdered,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.00,0:19:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he was drawing a picture on the deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.82,0:19:27.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bread pieces are sometimes used\Nas erasers for charcoal sketches,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.84,0:19:30.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I hear that these pieces\Noften fall into artists' cuffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.05,0:19:35.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When he stabbed Mr. Gozo,\Nthat piece of bread fell out of his cuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.10,0:19:38.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It fell onto Mr. Gozo's blood, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.31,0:19:43.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, this bread piece\Nhas a tiny bit of charcoal on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.39,0:19:46.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no doubt that it was\NIchiro-kun who dropped it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.79,0:19:49.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he has no motive!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.17,0:19:51.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro had no reason to kill Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.86,0:19:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I, myself, couldn't tell what\Nhis motive was until the very end.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.25,0:19:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until I saw something\Nin his room, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.16,0:20:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something in his room?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.83,0:20:03.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.25,0:20:07.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Ichiro-kun's motive\Nfor killing Mr. Gozo.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.13,0:20:10.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How is a picture his motive?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.92,0:20:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The answer is in the drawing itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.80,0:20:15.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see how...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.48,0:20:17.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.64,0:20:19.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.48,0:20:23.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! All these drawings are of Natsue!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.94,0:20:32.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro! Don't tell me you--
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.28,0:20:34.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.53,0:20:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro-kun was in love\Nwith Natsue-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.54,0:20:42.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.37,0:20:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard from Suzuki-san, the butler.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.17,0:20:49.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unable to reveal\Nyour feelings to Natsue-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.51,0:20:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you went to Mr. Gozo and--
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.56,0:20:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true! I asked him\Nto let me marry Natsue-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.47,0:20:58.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he wouldn't hear me out!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.60,0:21:02.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He refused to give his beloved\NNatsue-san to someone like me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.64,0:21:05.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And soon after that,\Nalmost as if to spite me,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.48,0:21:08.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he announced that Natsue-san\Nwas going to marry Takeshi-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.73,0:21:13.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then when he yelled at me yesterday
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.36,0:21:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while I was on the deck,\Ndrawing Natsue-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.29,0:21:19.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell him to give up\Nhis hopeless dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.39,0:21:22.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't forgive them!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.08,0:21:25.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not my grandfather, who refused\Nto let me marry Natsue-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.91,0:21:32.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nor Takeshi-san, who stole\Nmy Natsue-san away from me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.83,0:21:55.25,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just my imagination {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.37,0:22:05.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Playing with threads around my finger\Nwhile drinking lukewarm tea{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.72,0:22:14.06,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's walk lightly\Nto the bossa nova rhythm{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.18,0:22:19.06,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The puzzle pieces are in my hands{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.27,0:22:25.36,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's right... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.49,0:22:35.20,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was in the same place last week\Nbut with different clothes{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.54,0:22:42.63,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Step by step,\Nthere's no reason to be anxious{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.55,0:22:49.05,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Case by case,\NI don't care if you laugh{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.47,0:22:58.81,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Beyond the countless days,\Nshe's waiting for me{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.23,0:23:03.36,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I gotta go my own way {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.51,0:23:13.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.48,0:23:18.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you still feel the same way\Ntoward my grandfather and us?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.91,0:23:22.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am the son of Zaiki Isao,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.01,0:23:26.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who committed suicide after the\NHatamoto Group took over his company.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.25,0:23:30.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's true that I got close to you\Nbecause I hated your grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.37,0:23:33.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But ever since I met you...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.51,0:23:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The tragedy was caused\Nby a shy young man
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.56,0:23:43.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who was unable to put his\Nsecret thoughts into words...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.32,0:23:48.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ship is nearing Tokyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.47,0:23:52.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...while being bathed by the red sunset\Nthat is the sadness and despair
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.91,0:23:54.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of Ichiro-san and the\Nentire Hatamoto family.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.07,0:24:11.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She has...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.92,0:24:13.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Amnesia?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.47,0:24:16.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's him!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.14,0:24:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is the man from the racetrack
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.77,0:24:25.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after Maya-san?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.50,0:24:27.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.97,0:24:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Case of the\NMysterious Woman with Amnesia.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.33,0:24:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.60,0:24:51.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brooch.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.55,0:24:55.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode the old man finds himself in danger.
